#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.31:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.31:0.2"
msgid "3. Aṭṭhasatapariyāyavagga"
msgstr "3. The Explanation of the Hundred and Eight"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Nirāmisasutta"
msgstr "31. Spiritual"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi, bhikkhave, sāmisā pīti, atthi nirāmisā pīti, atthi nirāmisā "
"nirāmisatarā pīti;"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there is carnal rapture, spiritual rapture, and even more "
"spiritual rapture."

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.2"
msgid ""
"atthi sāmisaṃ sukhaṃ, atthi nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ, atthi nirāmisā nirāmisataraṃ "
"sukhaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"There is carnal pleasure, spiritual pleasure, and even more spiritual "
"pleasure."

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.3"
msgid ""
"atthi sāmisā upekkhā, atthi nirāmisā upekkhā, atthi nirāmisā nirāmisatarā "
"upekkhā;"
msgstr ""
"There is carnal equanimity, spiritual equanimity, and even more spiritual "
"equanimity."

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.4"
msgid ""
"atthi sāmiso vimokkho, atthi nirāmiso vimokkho, atthi nirāmisā nirāmisataro "
"vimokkho."
msgstr ""
"There is carnal liberation, spiritual liberation, and even more spiritual "
"liberation."

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.5"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sāmisā pīti?"
msgstr "And what is carnal rapture?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.6"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.7"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.8"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing. Sounds … Smells … Tastes …"

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.9"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.10"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.31:1.11"
msgid ""
"Yā kho, bhikkhave, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati pīti, ayaṃ vuccati, "
"bhikkhave, sāmisā pīti."
msgstr ""
"The rapture that arises from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is "
"called carnal rapture."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.236"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:2.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, nirāmisā pīti?"
msgstr "And what is spiritual rapture?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "sn36.31:2.3"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "sn36.31:2.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nirāmisā pīti."
msgstr "This is called spiritual rapture."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, nirāmisā nirāmisatarā pīti?"
msgstr "And what is even more spiritual rapture?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yā kho, bhikkhave, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato, dosā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ paccavekkhato, mohā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato uppajjati pīti, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nirāmisā nirāmisatarā "
"pīti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant who has ended the defilements reviews their mind free from "
"greed, hate, and delusion, rapture arises. This is called even more "
"spiritual rapture."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, sāmisaṃ sukhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is carnal pleasure?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:4.2"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "Mendicants, there are these five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.31:4.3"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:4.4"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing. Sounds … Smells … Tastes …"

msgctxt "sn36.31:4.5"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn36.31:4.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.31:4.7"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, "
"idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sāmisaṃ sukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The pleasure and happiness that arise from these five kinds of sensual "
"stimulation is called carnal pleasure."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:5.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is spiritual pleasure?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

msgctxt "sn36.31:5.3"
msgid ""
"Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter "
"and remain in the second absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of "
"immersion, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified mind, without "
"placing the mind and keeping it connected."

msgctxt "sn36.31:5.4"
msgid ""
"Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena "
"paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti "
"tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"And with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third "
"absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, ‘"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.’"

msgctxt "sn36.31:5.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nirāmisaṃ sukhaṃ."
msgstr "This is called spiritual pleasure."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.237"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:6.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, nirāmisā nirāmisataraṃ sukhaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is even more spiritual pleasure?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kho, bhikkhave, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato, dosā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ paccavekkhato, mohā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nirāmisā "
"nirāmisataraṃ sukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant who has ended the defilements reviews their mind free from "
"greed, hate, and delusion, pleasure and happiness arises. This is called "
"even more spiritual pleasure."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:7.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sāmisā upekkhā?"
msgstr "And what is carnal equanimity?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:7.2"
msgid "Pañcime, bhikkhave, kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "There are these five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.31:7.3"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:7.4"
msgid ""
"Cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"Sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing. Sounds … Smells … Tastes …"

msgctxt "sn36.31:7.5"
msgid ""
"kāyaviññeyyā phoṭṭhabbā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"Touches known by the body that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn36.31:7.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāmaguṇā."
msgstr "These are the five kinds of sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn36.31:7.7"
msgid ""
"Yā kho, bhikkhave, ime pañca kāmaguṇe paṭicca uppajjati upekkhā, ayaṃ "
"vuccati, bhikkhave, sāmisā upekkhā."
msgstr ""
"The equanimity that arises from these five kinds of sensual stimulation is "
"called carnal equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:8.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, nirāmisā upekkhā?"
msgstr "And what is spiritual equanimity?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:8.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā, dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā, adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, a mendicant enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without "
"pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "sn36.31:8.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nirāmisā upekkhā."
msgstr "This is called spiritual equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:9.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, nirāmisā nirāmisatarā upekkhā?"
msgstr "And what is even more spiritual equanimity?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:9.2"
msgid ""
"Yā kho, bhikkhave, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato, dosā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ paccavekkhato, mohā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato uppajjati upekkhā, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nirāmisā "
"nirāmisatarā upekkhā."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant who has ended the defilements reviews their mind free from "
"greed, hate, and delusion, equanimity arises. This is called even more "
"spiritual equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:10.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, sāmiso vimokkho?"
msgstr "And what is carnal liberation?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:10.2"
msgid "Rūpappaṭisaṃyutto vimokkho sāmiso vimokkho."
msgstr "Liberation connected with form is carnal."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:11.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, nirāmiso vimokkho?"
msgstr "And what is spiritual liberation?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:11.2"
msgid "Arūpappaṭisaṃyutto vimokkho nirāmiso vimokkho."
msgstr "Liberation connected with the formless is spiritual."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:12.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, nirāmisā nirāmisataro vimokkho?"
msgstr "And what is even more spiritual liberation?"

msgctxt "sn36.31:12.2"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, bhikkhave, khīṇāsavassa bhikkhuno rāgā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato, dosā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ paccavekkhato, mohā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ "
"paccavekkhato uppajjati vimokkho, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, nirāmisā "
"nirāmisataro vimokkho”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant who has ended the defilements reviews their mind free from "
"greed, hate, and delusion, liberation arises. This is called even more "
"spiritual liberation.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.31:12.3"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.31:12.4"
msgid "Aṭṭhasatapariyāyavaggo tatiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.238"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.31:13.1"
msgid "Sīvakaaṭṭhasataṃ bhikkhu,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.31:13.2"
msgid "pubbe ñāṇañca bhikkhunā;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.31:13.3"
msgid "Samaṇabrāhmaṇā tīṇi,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn36.31:13.4"
msgid "suddhikañca nirāmisanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn36.31:13.5"
msgid "Vedanāsaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on feeling are complete."
